=== TC-BH-001: HackerOne Web Application Bounty ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation

Simulation: Bounty hunting methodology for web target

Phase 1: Target Selection
  - Platform: HackerOne
  - Program: public, web application scope
  - Scope: *.target.com, excluding staging

Phase 2: Reconnaissance
  - Subdomain enumeration (search-first: amass, subfinder)
  - Technology fingerprinting (Wappalyzer patterns)
  - Endpoint discovery (waybackurls, gau)

Phase 3: Vulnerability Discovery
  - Priority P0: SSRF, RCE, Auth bypass
  - Priority P1: SQLi, XSS (stored), IDOR
  - Methodology: manual + automated (nuclei templates)

Phase 4: PoC Development
  - Minimal reproduction steps
  - Impact demonstration
  - CVSS scoring

Phase 5: Report Submission
  - Title: concise vulnerability description
  - Severity: CVSS-based
  - Steps to reproduce: numbered, minimal
  - Impact: business impact statement
  - Fix recommendation

Verification:
- Five-phase methodology followed ✓
- Priority-based vulnerability targeting ✓
- PoC development process defined ✓
- Report structure validated ✓

RESULT: PASS — bounty hunting methodology validated
Note: No real target tested; workflow and methodology confirmed
